      "content": "During the 35-day 2018â€“2019 shutdown, over 800,000 federal workersâ€”including janitors, security guards, and cafeteria staffâ€”were furloughed or required to work without immediate pay. All received full back pay within days of the shutdownâ€™s conclusion, per GEFTA.",
